1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:04,200
This diagram shows Skill's three-tier progressive structure.

2
00:00:04,150 --> 00:00:08,525
The top tier lists only the skill name and a one-line description.

3
00:00:08,525 --> 00:00:11,462
The middle tier is the method skeleton.

4
00:00:11,462 --> 00:00:14,587
The bottom tier holds the full details.

5
00:00:14,587 --> 00:00:18,862
The AI only loads the next tier when it actually needs it.

6
00:00:18,862 --> 00:00:26,225
That's why a Skill isn't just a longer prompt—it's a capability governance mechanism built around token efficiency.

